<Author>Ed-London
<Content>Nice comfortable hotel, excellent staff, good rates, average location. The Room:The Confortel Auditori was very pleasant. It鈥檚 clean and modern and the room was decent for a 3*. We had a proper double bed - rather than 2 single beds joined together - which made a nice change. The bathroom was also nice and ours (at least) was a decent size. We didn鈥檛 like the pillows, but they weren鈥檛 so bad we felt a need to complain either鈥?As you鈥檒l have read elsewhere 鈥?the minibar in the rooms are free, which is a nice touch, and come with Water (still  sparkling), Beer (one regular, one non-alcohol), Coke (regular  diet) and Juice (orange and another). This gets restocked daily. However, there is no coffee / tea / kettle in the room which always bugs me. Also, worth noting that the hotel doesn鈥檛 have 鈥減roper鈥?room service, they have a contract with a local Pizza chain who will provide delivered pizza / drinks etc 鈥?didn鈥檛 really bother us but means there鈥檚 no room service breakfast for example. Note that we were on the 6th floor (highest apart from the roof) and all the surrounding buildings are the same height, so no views.The Amenities:Breakfast (included in our Rate) was decent, although given the hotel wasn鈥檛 too busy when we were there, the seating was rather limited and tended to fill up by about 8:30 / 9am each morning. The food selection was good however and was replenished through the service period. The staff in the hotel were pleasant, in particular the front desk were very helpful in assisting us with restaurant reservations and similar. There are also two free PC鈥檚 in the lobby, and free wireless access in the rooms. On the downside however 鈥?there were a few times when the Confortel showed its budget hotel roots 鈥?requests for tissues, umbrellas (on the first day at least) and power adapters were not met. Lastly there鈥檚 a small pool (**small** - a splash pool) on the roof, but we were there in late October and it was too cold to use. The Location:Probably the only (real) minor downside to the Confortel Auditori is its location 鈥?it is a bit of a way away from La Rambla (25 minute brisk walk) and the port areas (20 鈥?30 minutes). We don鈥檛 mind as we like walking 鈥?but older visitors or families with kids may not be so keen. The local area is peaceful 鈥?mainly residential 鈥?but on the flip side there weren鈥檛 many (nice) restaurants or bars nearby. However, there is a Metro station 5 minutes away, and a further two stations (different lines) within 10 minutes. The tramline is also 10 minutes walk. A major bus depot is next door. The nearest Metro station (Arc de Triomf) is also an FGC  RENFE (railway line) station. So transport links are good. The Metro system is very efficient 鈥?though there鈥檚 lots (and lots) of steps.Overall:For the competitive rates we paid for our booking (it was low season) we really haven鈥檛 got any complaints about the Confortel. When we return to Barcelona (what a great city!) I would strongly imagine we will stay here again!General recommendations:We would recommend walking 鈥?the Historic / Old town is actually quite small, and is interesting to walk around. Restaurants 鈥?We were lucky to have a local friend recommend some places. Elx in the Maremagnum. Agua in Port Olimpica. Merendero de la Mari in Port Vell. All 3 were really excellent up market restaurants. 
