<Content>Good Hotel, good position Good, clean, modern hotel. Located about a five minute walk to the nearest metro station arc de triumph so you are able to tour the whole city easily. We purchased a ten trip ticket for 7 euros or you can do one for three days for 14 euros.Free minibar in the room comprises 2 still waters, 2 sparking waters, 2 orange juice, 2 coca cola and 2 beers. These are stocked up every morning when the room is cleaned.The room is modern and clean with a flat screen tv on the wall. Only a couple of english speaking channels though.Bathroom has a large shower and plenty of complementary toiletries.If you are wanting a full english breakfast then this is not the place for you. Cereals, toast, ham, cheese, croissants and a selection cakes. Juice and coffee is available.There are 2 free internet connections located in the lobby. Handy if you need and info or just want to keep in touch. There is a very small gym and an equally small pool on the roof, which is closed at this time of year.Warned about pickpockets but we did not have a problem. Took the tourist bus which costs 20 euros for the day and you can hop on and off as much as you like. You catch it at the top of Las Ramblas, which is within walking distance of the hotel.Overall very pleased with the hotel it is an excellent base for seeing Barcelona. 
