<Content>Very pleasant and enjoyable experience A group of sixteen of us spent five nights at this hotel at the end of October 2007 and I think that we were all well pleased with the experience. A few of our number had the ocassional breakfast in the hotel and found the food plentiful and of good quality but most of us gave it a miss because it added significantly to the cost. Alternative breakfast - On coming out of the hotel turn right and walk up to the next junction - then take the first left and continue down that road for approx 600-800m, towards the city centre, crossing a few crossroads, until you see a bar / cafe called Bar Fausto - they do a good English breakfast for 7.5 E or a continental for 5 E.The hotel staff were very pleasant, helpful and English speaking. Freebies such as the mini-bar, free mineral water (available in upper foyer) and internet access were well worth having. The bedrooms were very clean and comfortable, although those facing inwards were perhaps, less appealing. The security safe in each bedroom were also useful. The hotel is well situated, in a realtively quiet street but within walking distance (15 mins) of the city centre. One minor disadvantage is the lack of restaurants, as opposed to bar / cafes, within a mile of the hotel - we found ouselves having to wander to the city cntre most evenings. All in all, a very pleasant stay and I'm sure that all sixteen of us would recommend this hotel. 
