<Content>Good Hotel, Location a bit far We stayed at the hotel for 5 nights during the first week of June, 2007. The hotel is relatively new and modern.It is a bit expensive 139 Euro per night including breakfast.A couple of important tips:1. There are no smoking rooms - ask for one if you do not smoke.2. There are rooms that face the street (very noisy) and there are rooms that face the interior (no view - and quite). 3. The minibar is free it has water and other drinks.4. The pool is a joke - it is as big as a Jacuzzi.5. The fitness center is very basically equipped.6. Breakfast was adequate, a buffet that has no hot food. mainly cold meat, cheese, fruit, pastries, cold cereal etc..7. If you bring a laptop, there is free wireless internet throughout the hotel, but be advised the line is very slow (about 50 Kb/s) analog modem speed.8. Ask the staff to send you beach towels that you can use both on the roof solarium, or if you care to go to the beach (a goof idea!).9. The water pressure and hot water are good, the mirror was cool 鈥?it has a heating element that makes sure that it does not get covered in fog.The room size is typical European - a bit on the small size, but big enough. The bathroom had a peculiar shower stall that while taking a shower there was no way from avoiding soaking the bathroom floor - an obvious design flaw. There is a safety deposit box in the room, but note that it is not connected to the wall - someone can just take the safe away (another design flaw). The receptionists we talked to were polite but not very efficient and didn鈥檛 know English well.Location: It is located near the Arc de Triumf. It is about a 20-25 minute walk from the Sagrada Familia and the Ramblas. The metro is nearby if you prefer to use it.We took the taxi to every location we needed.I recommend this Hotel after saying all the above. 
