<Content>Great business hotel This hotel is nothing grand or fancy, if you want that go to a Sheraton or a Hyatt or whatever. But if you need a comfortable, clean, modern hotel, in a convenient location and with excellent facilities, this is a trully great hotel.The Confortel Auditori seems to be brand new. It is absolutely spotlessly clean and very very modern. The rooms are a good size - Queen bed, desk, armchair, plenty of room for an open suitcase etc. The bathroom doesn't have a seperate bath and shower, but who cares. The water pressure and shower head are excellent. Its also got one of those mirrors that demists itself - a feature I think sll hotels should implement. The floors are parquet, so no nasty stained carpets.Wireless internet is free, and so is the mini-bar!!! Its got 2 juices, 2 beers, 2 bottles of still water and 2 bottles of sparkling mineral water, and its restocked daily. This is the sort of great feature that will bring back guests again and again. The fitness room is small, but adequate. Its got 2 excercise bikes, a treadmill and a few weights.Location is fine since it is very close to a metro station which gets you anywhere quickly.Breakfast is good. Nothing fancy, but perfectly fine. A few other nice touches - there are small TVs in the breakfast area where you canwatch the morning news while you eat. Great if you're alone on business. Also there are a couple of internet PCs in the lobby, also for free of course.I will definately stay in this hotel again if I am in Barcelona. 
