<Content>Have only good things to say about this hotel! Stayed at this hotel back in September for 5 nights and was extremely impressed by it. The hotel is in a really nice quarter of Barcelona and is very centrally situated. It's a pleasant 15-20 minute walk from Plaza de Catalunya, about half an hour's walk from the beach and Port Olympic and the tube station is 2 mins away. The room itself was very nice  clean and the decoration throughout the hotel is very modern. The facilities were good - there's a small gym in the basement and a very small swimming pool on the roof. The pool had closed already when we stayed (it closes at the beginning of September) but it was still nice to sit out on the sunbeds by the pool for an hour in the evening. As we had room only, we only paid for breakfast once - they had a very nice buffet with lots of options. One of the most impressive things about the hotel was the free mini bar. It was stocked up with soft drinks/water/beer (no other alcoholic drinks) every day at no charge and there were fridges all over the hotel with free bottles of water. For the price I paid, I was extremely satisfied with this hotel, although I possibly wouldn't pay the standard hotel rate - It's definitely worth surfing the web to get some good deals! 
