<Author>thirtysomethingbloke
<Content>Fantastic Hotel for the Price Pre-booked via ---- at 拢 35 per person per night (bed and breakfast in a twin room), this hotel represented excellent value for money. As requested when booking, we had been given rooms on an upper floor. The Hotel was obviously new and the rooms were very spacious and comfortable. The free safe and minibar were also very welcome, especially as the minibar was topped up daily. The Plasma screen TVs looked cool too, although there was not a great choice of English-speaking channels. We were not in Barcelona to watch TV though!This Hotel proved to be a very good base for a long weekend stay - just outside of the throbbing centre of Barcelona but close enough to walk. The Placa de Catalunya and Sagrada Familia are about a 15-20 min walk away from the hotel and the harbour area was around 20-25 mins walk. The El Prat Airport bus drops passengers off at the Placa de Catalunya so we had lazily decided to take a taxi transfer to the hotel instead, paying 35 EUROS from the airport(but only charged 27 EUROS by a rank taxi on the return journey). The Girona/Ryanair airport bus apparently goes to the Nord station which is probably less than a 2 minute walk from the hotel. There is also a taxi rank at the Nord station.I suppose the walk to/from la Rambla can become a bit of a trek after doing it a few times, but the hotel is in a decent area and we could have taken the metro (less than 5 mins away from the hotel) if we had wanted.We found the staff on reception generally friendly and helpful. A couple of the breakfast staff looked a bit miserable at times but it was busy I suppose. The buffet breakfasts offered a decent and plentiful choice and I'm glad we pre-booked, although the bakery opposite the hotel also looked very good.Overall, this is an excellent hotel if you don't mind a little bit of a walk. I would certainly stay here again and recommend both the hotel and the great city of Barcelona to anyone. 
